# TTS.action
#
# Action server: /tts  (text_to_speech node)
#
# Synthesises the given text and plays it through the configured backend
# (naoqi_ros, kokoro_local, kokoro_pepper, elevenlabs_local, or
# elevenlabs_pepper). The action blocks until playback is fully complete,
# making it safe to sequence in a BehaviorTree after ConversationManager.
#
# The text is split into sentences internally; each sentence is queued and
# played in order. Barge-in (VAD-based interruption) is still honoured —
# if the user speaks during playback the remaining sentences are dropped and
# the action returns success=true.

# ── Goal ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Text to synthesise and speak. May contain multiple sentences.
string text

---

# ── Result ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# True if playback completed (or was cleanly interrupted by barge-in)
bool success
# "OK" on success; human-readable error description otherwise
string message

---

# ── Feedback ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Current playback stage
# "queuing"  – sentences are being added to the playback queue
# "speaking" – audio is actively playing
string status
